"n.门厅，休息室 【英】 n. 门厅，休息室(an entrance hall or lobby) n. (戏院或旅馆的)门厅, 休息室 = hall = lobby 【记】读: for爷(爷)－为了让爷爷休息一下－门厅 【记】源自fire 有火炉的房间，发音也象fire；音：飞跃(跃发yao的音)，你成功飞跃彼岸了就可以到休息室休息了 foyer (n.)  1859, from French foyer ""green room, room for actors when not on stage,"" literally ""fireplace,"" from Old French foier ""furnace, stove, hearth, fireplace"" (12c.), from Latin focarium, noun use of neuter of adjective focarius ""having to do with the hearth,"" from focus ""hearth, fireplace"" (see focus (n.))."
